          <h3>How can I verify the authenticity of handmade crafts in Bandra?</h3>
          <p>Look for slight variations in design (machine-made items are perfectly uniform), ask about the making process, check for quality materials, and buy from verified artisans with established reputations. Many authentic craftspeople are happy to explain their techniques.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What are the typical price ranges for handmade crafts in Bandra?</h3>
          <p>Prices vary widely based on complexity, materials, and artisan experience. Small items (keychains, earrings): ₹200-800. Medium pieces (wall art, pottery): ₹1,000-5,000. Large or intricate items (paintings, furniture): ₹5,000-50,000+. Custom work typically costs 20-30% more.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do artisans in Bandra accept custom orders for bulk purchases?</h3>
          <p>Yes, most established artisans welcome bulk orders for weddings, corporate events, or retail. They often offer discounts for larger quantities. It's best to discuss requirements, timelines, and pricing well in advance, especially during peak seasons.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does it typically take to complete a custom craft order?</h3>
          <p>Timeline depends on complexity and current workload. Simple customizations: 3-7 days. Medium complexity items: 1-3 weeks. Elaborate pieces or bulk orders: 4-8 weeks. Always confirm timelines when placing orders, especially for special occasions.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Are there workshops where I can learn traditional craft techniques?</h3>
          <p>Yes, many Bandra artisans offer workshops and classes. Check community centers, art cafés, and individual artist studios for scheduled sessions. Topics include pottery, painting, jewelry making, textile crafts, and more. Workshops range from ₹500-3,000 per session.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

